Class GraphAlgos

  • java.lang.Object
    • GraphAlgos
  • public class GraphAlgos
extends java.lang.Object
    The graphAlgos class is used to create methods to search, assemble, analyze, and organize data into graphs and other representations.

      • mst

        private int mst​(java.lang.String[] vertices,
                java.lang.String start,
                int[][] weights)
        The mst method is used to assemble a minimum spanning tree of the passed list of vertices. This method uses a brute force form of prim's algorithm. The runtime does take upward of 3 minutes to return the total weight on my personal machine.
        Parameters:
        vertices - The param vertices is the list of interconnected vertices.
        start - The start string is where in the list to start the MST at.
        weights - The weights param is a 2d array of ints that represents the weights of moves.
        Returns:
        The return is the total weight of the MST.
